text: Clark County is a county in the U.S. state of Ohio. As of the 2020 census, the population was 136,001. Its county seat is Springfield. The county was created on March 1, 1818. It was named for General George Rogers Clark, a hero of the American Revolution. == References == Category:1810s establishments in Ohio Category:1818 establishments in Ohio Category:Ohio counties
title: Clark County, Ohio
